===Etymology===

:Late Latin '''hypocorisma''' is from the Greek noun ('''hypokorisma''') that is from the verb ('''hypokorizesthai''' = 'to call by pet names'). The Greek verb ''hypokorizesthai'' is compounded from ([[hypo]]- = 'under') + ('''korizesthai''' = 'to [[caress]]'), from ('''koros''') '[[boy]]', ('''kore''') '[[girl]]'.

===Meaning===

#a pet name
#the use of pet names 

